        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 12:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Willis to Ida to Lambertville. Movement
was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Carleton, Temperance, Ida, Luna Pier, Maybee, Lambertville,
La Salle, Erie, Rockwood, South Rockwood, Estral Beach, Newport,
Toledo Beach, Woodland Beach, Stony Point, Bolles Harbor, Samaria,
Scofield, and Detroit Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
